:POLL
Do you think setting can function as a horror novel's primary antagonist?
Yes and Mexican Gothic proves it definitively
Sometimes, when the writing is skilled enough to sustain it
Rarely, setting works better as atmosphere than as antagonist
No, I need a character or creature as the source of fear
